<item>
            <title>[SANDBOX-337] Wrong value for Vertex degree</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SANDBOX-337</link>
                <project id="12310491" key="SANDBOX">Commons Sandbox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi folk, I&apos;m doing a tests case for the class BaseMutableGraph, in order to upgrade our testcase suite. I think that our implementation of vertex degree is wrong.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;according with &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glossary_of_graph_theory#Adjacency_and_degree&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glossary_of_graph_theory#Adjacency_and_degree&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;The degree, or valency, dG(v) of a vertex v in a graph G is the number of edges incident to v, with loops being counted twice. A vertex of degree 0 is an isolated vertex. A vertex of degree 1 is a leaf. In the labelled simple graph example, vertices 1 and 3 have a degree of 2, vertices 2, 4 and 5 have a degree of 3, and vertex 6 has a degree of 1. If E is finite, then the total sum of vertex degrees is equal to twice the number of edges.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;so for a complete graph with 5 nodes, each vertex has a degree of 4. Instead our implementation returns 8.&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
IMHO this is wrong. WDYT?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have a nice week end&lt;/p&gt;</description>
