                            <comment id="13059117" author="simone.tripodi" created="Sat, 2 Jul 2011 20:02:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting! It sounds something it has definitively be fixed &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
fixed on r1142289, can you please update and confirm that it works now?&lt;br/&gt;
please resolve the issue once verified!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13059230" author="marco.speranza" created="Sun, 3 Jul 2011 16:52:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Simo, I checked out the trunk and for Undirect graph seems ok.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IMHO we have to modify in the same way also DirectMutableGraph:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    /**
     * {@inheritDoc}
     */
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; getDegree( V v )
    {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; getInDegree( v );
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;WDYT?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I added also a little patch with the test case and this modify.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ciao&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13059251" author="simone.tripodi" created="Sun, 3 Jul 2011 18:26:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch! &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure the modification you are proposing is 100% right, looks like for Directed graphs there are different opinions: take a look at this &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.utm.edu/departments/math/graph/glossary.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;article&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;degree&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The degree (or valence) of a vertex is the number of edge ends at that vertex. For example, in this graph all of the vertices have degree three.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In a digraph (directed graph) the degree is usually divided into the in-degree and the out-degree (&lt;b&gt;whose sum is the degree&lt;/b&gt; of the vertex in the underlying undirected graph).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Take also a look at this &lt;a href=&quot;http://reference.wolfram.com/mathematica/ref/VertexDegree.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;samples&lt;/a&gt; with directed graphs: for Vertex &lt;tt&gt;2&lt;/tt&gt;, that has &lt;tt&gt;deg+ = 2&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;deg- = 1&lt;/tt&gt;, the degree is &lt;tt&gt;2&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.algoritmica.org/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; I&apos;m reading (sorry, in Italian only) it is reported the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Il grado in uscita di un nodo &#232; pari al numero di archi uscenti da esso, mentre il grado in ingresso e dato dal numero di archi entranti. Il grado &#232; la somma del grado d&apos;ingresso e di quello d&apos;uscita&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13059282" author="marco.speranza" created="Sun, 3 Jul 2011 21:20:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK I agree with you. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, I removed the patch and tomorrow I&apos;ll finish the test case, in that way.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;bye bye &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
